    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no way to extend an existing query using `vim.treesitter.query.set`; it ignores all modelines passed to it, making extending existing queries programmatically harder than it needs to be.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither:\r\n1. `vim.treesitter.query.set` handles modelines, or\r\n2. `vim.treesitter.query.set` accepts a fourth optional argument that serves the same purpose as the modelines: `{ extends:bool?, inherits:string[]? }`\r\n\r\nI myself wanted to create a utility plugin that would generate highlight queries for `comment` parser from a user-supplied table in order to add new highlight keywords like `SAFETY`. Hardcoding new keywords into query files is not an option, and polluting user's config with queries is not ideal.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
